article.description: Malcolm leads Holy Cross over Army 78-75
article.headline: Malcolm leads Holy Cross over Army 78-75
article.linkText: Malcolm leads Holy Cross over Army 78-75
article.story: WEST POINT, N.Y. -- Malcolm Miller scored six of his 17 points with less than three minutes to play as Holy Cross overcame a 14-point deficit to defeat Army 78-75 Wednesday night. Army had its largest lead, 63-49 with 9:45 remaining. Holy Cross answered with a 21-6 run to take its first lead of the second half, 70-69 with 3:13 left. Miller scored twice and his two free throws gave the Crusaders a 76-73 lead with 31 seconds left. Justin Burrell and Anthony Thompson each made one of two free throws to cap the scoring for Holy Cross (8-9, 2/3 Patriot League). Eric Green added 11 points with 10 rebounds for Holy Cross. Tanner Plomb hit a career-high six 3-pointers on his way to a career-best 29 points to lead Army (8-8, 4-1). Dylan Cox, who scored eight of the last 10 points for the Black Knights, finished with 11 points.
